                "<b>Because</b> of he was ill, he didn't come.",
                "<b>Because</b> he was ill, he didn't come.",
                "Because of + Noun; Because + Clause."
              ],
              [
                "<b>Unless</b> you don't study, you will fail.",
                "<b>Unless</b> you study, you will fail.",
                "Unless = If not (already negative)."
              ],
              [
                "I will wait <b>unless</b> you come.",
                "I will wait <b>until</b> you come.",
                "Until = Time; Unless = Condition."
              ],
              [
                "He is <b>both</b> smart <b>as well as</b> kind.",
                "He is <b>both</b> smart <b>and</b> kind.",
                "Both...and = correct pair."
              ],
              [
                "<b>No sooner</b> I reached <b>when</b> it rained.",
                "<b>No sooner</b> did I reach <b>than</b> it rained.",
                "No sooner...than (with inversion)."
              ],
              [
                "<b>Hardly</b> I slept <b>than</b> phone rang.",
